UBA GHANA PRESENTS A LAPTOP TO BEST GRADUATING STUDENT IN BANKING AND FINANCE
Mr. Irwin J. Yama a foreign student from Gabon studying at the Catholic Institute of Business and Technology Ghana on Friday February 5,2016, received a laptop from UBA Ghana for emerging Best Banking and Finance graduating student from the School. Victoria Attipoe, Corporate Business Office Manager, Heritage Tower and Johnson Olakunmi, Head Digital Banking presented the award on behalf of the MD/CEO Mrs Abiola Bawuah at the 3rd Graduation Ceremony of the School in Accra Ghana. Irwin expressed his appreciation to the bank for the award and promised to make good use of the laptop.
